title: Crocs Women's Jayna Slip-On Loafer
reviewText: I've worn three pairs of black Crocs down to nubs.  I wear them all year round; dressed up, dressed down, as slippers, with and without socks--they are my default footwear.  Skirts, dresses, pants, shorts, capris--Crocs go with everything.  There's not another shoe on the market that offers the Big Three of comfort, support, and traction with a bit of style. I was thrilled to find them on Amazon, and at such great prices.  When I finally pitched my last pair of worn to shreds Crocs, I ordered the Jaynas--a new style for me.  I love them!My shoe size is between a 7.5 and an 8.  I purchased an 8 in the Jayna and it's a bit big, but doesn't fall off my foot.  Actually, since I'll be wearing these this summer, the looseness will be a good thing.  When I put on the new ones, I realized just how worn my old ones were.  These are springy, and COMFORTABLE!  I'll probably purchase these in 7s next fall.

reviewText: This is a darling little clutch, and much better looking than the picture. title: Buxton Heiress Ensemble Clutch
reviewText: I always come back to Buxton for wallets.  This one has a place for everything, and I do mean everything!  I really like the currency compartment--there are two slots for bills and a center zippered compartment for coins, receipts, or large denominations.  There's also a change pouch in front for easy access.  There are almost enough card slots, and there are a number of plastic sleeves if you run out of slots.  For some reason the slots are not of uniform size and I had to do some finagling to make some of my cards fit.  I also wish the snap flap went over the currency compartment so I didn't have to keep it zipped, but I'll get used to it, and I'm sure the leather slots will loosen up with use.After an exhaustive online and in store search, I've decided that this clutch gives the best bang for the buck.  Mine is red, and it's a rich, not fire engine color.  I'm very pleased.

reviewText: I'm known as the Croc Queen in some circles.  I've completely worn out several pairs, which is unusual for me.  Usually I discard shoes a after a couple of years because of style, not wear and tear.  Crocs are different.  Their style is timeless, and they're so COMFORTABLE!The Kadees are a new style for me. title: BEARPAW Women's Emma Short Boot
reviewText: This has been an awful winter in my part of the country. We've had weeks of zero and subzero temperatures, snow, ice, more snow, and did I mention how cold it's been?  I have a shoe rack full of boots, but the ones I go to day in and day out are my Bearpaws.  I don't even wear socks with them, and they keep my feet toasty warm.I've had these in the tall version, in light blue, for many years and keep them by the back door.  They're getting pretty ratty and the color is unsuitable for anything except jeans.  I'm so sick of having cold feet, and of scavenging through my boots and shoes to find something appropriate for the weather and the day's demands, so I broke down and ordered the short black ones. Bless Amazon, they were here in two days and I'm wiggling my toes in them right now.  They're as comfortable as slippers, and presentable enough to wear in public with long pants and leggings.  The only thing I don't like is the enormous Bearpaw logo on the backs, but the pluses outweigh the advertising a thousandfold.  These are not glamorous boots.  They're wide and clunky, but oh, so cozy and I'm thrilled!The soles of a sand colored pair I had for a couple of years disintegrated, but the soles of my new ones seem to be made of a different material, as do the soles of my blue pair.  Even if they don't last, they've been worth their weight in gold this winter!

reviewText: I'm a devotee of big bags, and this one is a tad small for my taste.  It's an appearance thing; this bag holds plenty. The bag is shallow enough that you can see everything inside, which is nice if you, like I, have to scrabble around to find your phone before the caller hangs up.  So size matters, but not so much for this bag.It's definitely a handheld bag--there's no shoulder strap and the handles aren't long enough to go over the shoulder. I'm going to keep it and use it for going out or to stick in my tote bag, but this isn't my favorite purse.

I looked at the label: it said XXL. They must've been going by Chinese sizes, not American women's larger frames. :(I ended up giving it to my housemate - she's skin and bones (literally), and it fits 'as it should' on her.This shirt, though beautiful, is NOT a "Plus Size", by any stretch of the imagination. title: Rothco VINTAGE PARATROOPER FATIGUE
reviewText: These pants are awesome. They look nice, and can be worn around the house while chilling, or worn for the zombie apocolypse. Either way I'm covered with these pants. They are extremely comfortable, and functional with lots of pockets. Very similar to what I wore while in the Army, except for the fact that they aren't a button fly, these pants use a zipper instead. They are fairly well made and have so far held up to my abuse of them. One downfall - made in China. I'd rather they were made in the U.S. Also know this, these pants have what are similar in a way to drawstrings on the sides (as do actual military issued pants - same system). So for example size medium runs from a 31-35 inch waist. I am 6 ft tall, 175 lbs. I normally wear a 32 waist. I originally ordered a large, but they were way too big for me. I now go with the medium. I pull the drawstring mechanism on the sides to tighten them up a bit, and I also wear a belt. The fit is just right. I originally bought one pair of these. I've grown to like them so much I own a half dozen pairs now.

reviewText: I bought these for my wife to spice things up a bit. As a bonus I thought that maybe she'd like them and find them comfortable. I was hoping for kind of an old school, traditional / conservative look. They do look great on her, as everything does. However, they're made of a rather thin material, and simply weren't quite as sexy as I had imagined. title: SPANX HIGH - WAISTED BODY SHAPING
reviewText: I've heard a lot about this brand over the years, but I never bought any products - probably b/c they are much pricier than those made by competitors. But I bought a few polyester/spandex blend wrap dresses at post-xmas sales, and so I decided to invest in a pair of these high-waist tights, in the hope that some of my lumpier spots could be smoothed out. Mission accomplished! At the moment, I am 20 pounds heavier than I should be. Although these tights only take off a couple of pounds, visually, they certainly do help to create the illusion of a more fit and toned physique.  In selecting a size, I used the height and weight size chart provided on the Amazon page, and that worked out just fine.I really appreciate the design of the crotch panels, which ensures that the tights do not rip. title: Squeem "Perfect Waist" Firm Compression Waist Cincher Shapewear, Cotton & Rubber
reviewText: First, thank you to the hundreds of other reviewers who took the time to describe their perceptions of this product. Your reviews were very helpful in guiding me to select the appropriate size of this waist cincher. It is definitely sturdier than similar products I own. I like that there are two rows of eyes in which to affix the hooks. Right now, I am using the looser setting, but it is nice to know that the item will continue to fit once I lose 10-15 pounds, too. As advertised, this cincher narrows the waist and creates a more-hourglass shape. I find the item to be very comfortable - I can bend over repeatedly yet this stays in place and the bottom doesn't flip up, the way it does with other shapewear. The item is made of a rubbery material, which is probably why it is so flexible and strong. This has a downside: although I don't notice that I am perspiring when I am wearing the item, when I take it off, my skin is definitely clammy.The more significant limitation is something that could cause a wearer of this item great embarrassment. I discovered that this is not a good item to wear when exerting oneself - not because it is difficult to move in (quite the contrary), but because when the rubber heats up against the skin, it gives off a horrid burned rubber smell that others notice. I really wish I had anticipated that problem. Now that I know, I will probably reserve this cincher for home use only, and wear a Rago when out in public.

title: Bella Vita Women's Transit II Plus Knee-High Boot
reviewText: I have, for better or worse, wide feet and thick calves. To find a boot that looks attractive -- even sexy -- yet fits me well is a rare treat. Across the holidays, I had bought a few new dresses for work, but I live in a wintry climate, and so I really wanted to get a pair of tall boots that I could wear at the office. These fit my feet and my calves very well. Although some other reviewers were disappointed that these boots weren't leather, I am actually pleased that they aren't, as it is easy to wipe off salt and other winter grime with a wet cloth in order to make the boots look good as new. They also seem to be water-resistant - no leaks yet:)To address potential purchasers' concerns about the size of the calf/shaft of the boot: try unbuckling all the outside buckles before zipping up the boots, then re-buckling them. The parts of the boot that go into the buckles have three holes precut, each about 1/2 inch apart. You may need to zip and then set the buckles at the loosest setting the first time you wear them. But I found that the leather-look fabric stretches out a bit after a few hours of wear. So the next time I wore the boots, I could zip them up without unbuckling. Then I was able to tighten up the buckle setting so the boots did not sag down.One important thing to be aware of, though, is that these boots are completely smooth on the bottom. The artwork on the soles is nifty, but it doesn't add any traction at all. So be super-careful if you are going to wear these boots in rainy, snowy, or icy weather.Also, on days when I have to do a lot of standing or walking at work, I've learned that these boots are not particularly comfortable. I bought some gel insoles and hope this solves the problem.

title: Rainkist Umbrellas Bubble
reviewText: I have this issue with umbrellas' that can't withstand wind. I mean, lets face it, most times when it rains, the wind is not too far behind it. So, it's now 2014 and people whom make umbrella's still have not decided to mass produce umbrellas that can withstand wind, so the umbrella doesn't bend or worse, break!The first time I got to try this baby, it was a rainy day with of course- WIND! So, I had to place it away after only 3 minutes of use and just get soaked, as the wind caused the umbrella to unhinge it's self. I was pissed, as I thought it was broken, but thank goodness, upon further inspection once I was safely inside and out of the windy rain, the metal lines that keep the umbrella up and shaped just popped out of their respective slots at the bottom. Small favors guys, small favors.Honestly, this is the first time I've spent over 10 bucks for an umbrella. I kinda think it's ridiculous to spend over that much for things that have proven to not be so sturdy and last long. No wonder my most people just wear their hoodies and weather out the storm as umbrellas are a pain. I can't see myself spending 50 to 100 dollars on an umbrella, that's just ridiculous in and of its self!So, this umbrella gets 4 stars. Why?My positives:- It's purple.-It's cute.- I can look through the umbrella, know where I'm going while managing to stay dry.Negatives:It's kind of big for my taste, there for it doesn't fit in my backpack or purse/bag, so you have to lug it around.-The structure is flimsy, so it's only good for days where it's JUST raining and nothing more. And seeing as I live in New England (Massachusetts to be exact), I suppose that will be far and in-between rainy days, like Summer rains. I guess I'll have to buy a small portable umbrella that fits in my purse and can withstand a little wind for the unexpected rainy days.

reviewText: I have been ever more disenfranchised with the cheap materials that pass for clothing product these days; the number of returns that I do is astronomical because of that. Things always look so cute in the pics but then when they get here, surprise! It sucks because of cheap shabby thin material, time and time again. Don't get me wrong, there are some successes with clothing on here but they have to get returned at least half the time. Well not only is the material quality on this garment, but there are two layers of it so you don't have to worry about being see-through. It is just as cute as in the pic if not more and I can't wait to wear it to the Farmer's Market to shop. It will look brilliant with one of my other good purchases which is the "Plus Size Top, In Soft Knit, The Perfect Cotton V-Neck Tee" from Woman Within; wear the melon or teal with a cute scarf and some cute sandals.
